.TH SHOWTERM "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
showterm \- Pure-shell showterm client for terminal session recording
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B showterm
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B showterm
is a simple Linux-only pure-shell showterm client for recording and sharing terminal sessions. It provides an alternative to the Ruby-based showterm without requiring Ruby.
.PP
The script records terminal sessions and uploads them to showterm.io for sharing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B showterm
Start recording a terminal session
.TP
.B showterm bash
Record a bash session
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/showterm/settings.conf
User configuration file for showterm preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
